  "texts": [
    "A Bellman equation is used at each state to get the estimated future state and reward that will be compared with other states.where the updater or new Q-value is Q new s t, a t. γ is a discount factor and demonstrates the importance of future rewards to the current state with ∈ (0, 1].",
    "r t+1 is the reward received by the agent at time t + 1 while performing an action (a) to move from one state to another.",
    "max Q s t+1, a t+1 is the maximum Q-value of the state s t+1 with action a t+1 at time t + 1.",
    "The agent generates the new action a t according to the current state s t using Eq.",
    "(33), it will give order to the environment to do the new state and reward s t+1 and r t+1 respectively."
